The paper discusses link adaptation techniques for improving the performance of multicarrier communication systems, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The paper also proposes novel optimization algorithms for maximizing throughput and minimizing transmit power, which falls under the category of control systems (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper mentions simulation results, which suggests a focus on multimedia systems (cs.MM) and machine learning (cs.LG) for evaluating the proposed algorithms.
